{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who embezzled 25000 dollars to pay off personal debts. While this is a serious breach of trust by a professional accountant, there are significant mitigating factors, including the absolute lack of a prior criminal record and the partial repayment of the stolen funds already made. The courtroom interruption from a spectator suggesting a 10-year sentence is entirely disregarded as an irrelevant emotional outburst. Given the circumstances and mitigating factors, a lenient but consequential sentence is warranted to provide both punishment and the opportunity to make full restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
